Former DA leader Mmusi Maimane. JOHANNESBURG - Mmusi Maimane has lost his urgent bid to stop schools from reopening on Monday. The founder of the One South Africa movement approached the Constitutional Court directly to hear his case. READ: Alert level 3: Reopening of schools delayed Maimane cited poor sanitation and infrastructure, overcrowding, and staff shortages as some of the reasons why schools should remain closed but the court dismissed his application, saying it is not urgent. Schools are set to open for Grades 12 and 7 on Monday 8 June after several teacher unions and were concerned about schools' readiness to receive pupils and teachers. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.